            <li><b>Wang</b> &mdash; Intermediate Structural Analysis, chapter on the Muller-Breslau Principle. McGraw-Hill.</li>
            <li><b>Virtual Labs (IIT)</b> &mdash; Structural Analysis: Influence Lines, sa-nitk.vlabs.ac.in.</li>
          </ul></div>
        </section>

        <!-- ============ EXPERIMENT 6 — EULER BUCKLING ============ -->
        <section class="exp" id="exp-6">
          <h2 class="exp-head">6 &middot; Euler column buckling</h2>
          <div class="exp-sub">Critical load and critical stress versus slenderness ratio for four end conditions, with the buckled mode shape</div>
          <div class="secbar">
            <button class="stab on" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="proc">Procedure</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
            <button class="stab" data-sec="ref">References</button>
          </div>

          <div class="sec aim on"><div class="prose">To compute the Euler critical buckling load of a slender column for pinned, fixed-fixed, fixed-free and fixed-pinned end conditions, to plot the critical stress against the slenderness ratio, and to mark the slenderness limit beyond which Euler theory applies.</div></div>

          <div class="sec theory"><div class="prose">
            <p>A straight elastic column under axial compression remains straight until the load reaches a critical value, at which it suddenly bows sideways &mdash; <b>buckling</b>. Euler solved the governing differential equation EI y'' = &minus;P y for a pin-ended strut and obtained the smallest non-trivial load:</p>
            <div class="eqblock">P(cr) = pi&sup2; E I / (K L)&sup2; &nbsp;&nbsp;(I = A r&sup2;, r = radius of gyration)</div>
            <p>The <b>effective length factor</b> K captures the end restraints: K = 1 for pinned-pinned, K = 0.5 for fixed-fixed, K = 2 for fixed-free (a flagpole), and K is about 0.7 for fixed-pinned. Dividing by area and writing the <b>slenderness ratio</b> lambda = K L / r gives the critical (buckling) stress:</p>
            <div class="eqblock">sigma(cr) = P(cr)/A = pi&sup2; E / lambda&sup2;,&nbsp; lambda = K L / r</div>
            <p>Euler's hyperbola sigma(cr) = pi&sup2; E / lambda&sup2; is valid only while sigma(cr) stays below the yield (or proportional) limit; for stocky columns (small lambda) the column yields or crushes before it buckles, so the curve is capped at the yield stress. The boundary slenderness is lambda(c) = pi &middot; sqrt(E / sigma(y)). The solver draws this curve, marks the operating point for the chosen geometry, and animates the corresponding buckled mode shape.</p>
          </div></div>

          <div class="sec proc"><ol class="steps">
            <li>Open <b>Simulation</b>. Choose the <b>end condition</b>; the effective length factor K is shown in the menu.</li>
            <li>Set the <b>length</b> L, the section <b>radius of gyration</b> r, the cross-section <b>area</b> A, Young's modulus <b>E</b> and the yield stress fy.</li>
            <li>The panel computes the <b>slenderness ratio</b>, the <b>critical load</b> and the <b>critical stress</b>; the operating point is plotted on the Euler curve.</li>
            <li>Watch whether the point lies on the <b>Euler branch</b> (slender, buckling governs) or under the <b>yield cap</b> (stocky, yielding governs); the badge says which.</li>
            <li>Vary L and the end condition and see the critical load fall with the square of effective length; the buckled mode shape redraws to match the end restraints.</li>
          </ol></div>

          <div class="sec sim">
            <div class="layout">
              <div class="panel">
                <h3><span>Critical stress vs slenderness</span><span class="badge" id="ebStat">ready</span></h3>
                <canvas id="ebCv" width="680" height="430"></canvas>
                <div class="help"><b>Curve</b> is Euler's hyperbola capped at the yield stress; the vertical line is the slenderness boundary lambda(c). The marker is your column; the small inset is its buckled mode.</div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="panel">
                  <h3>Controls</h3>
                  <div class="row"><label>Ends</label>
                    <select id="ebEnd">
                      <option value="pp">Pinned - Pinned (K=1)</option>
                      <option value="ff">Fixed - Fixed (K=0.5)</option>
                      <option value="fp">Fixed - Pinned (K=0.7)</option>
                      <option value="fc">Fixed - Free (K=2)</option>
                    </select>
                  </div>
                  <div class="row"><label>Length m</label><input type="range" id="ebL" min="0.5" max="8" value="3" step="0.1"><span class="val" id="ebLv">3.0</span></div>
                  <div class="row"><label>r mm</label><input type="range" id="ebR" min="5" max="80" value="25" step="1"><span class="val" id="ebRv">25</span></div>
                  <div class="row"><label>A cm&sup2;</label><input type="range" id="ebA" min="5" max="120" value="30" step="1"><span class="val" id="ebAv">30</span></div>
                  <div class="row"><label>E GPa</label><input type="range" id="ebE" min="70" max="210" value="200" step="5"><span class="val" id="ebEv">200</span></div>
                  <div class="row"><label>fy MPa</label><input type="range" id="ebFy" min="150" max="450" value="250" step="10"><span class="val" id="ebFyv">250</span></div>
                  <div class="stats">
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">Slenderness K L/r</div><div class="v purple" id="ebLam">--</div></div>
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">Boundary lambda(c)</div><div class="v sm" id="ebLc">--</div></div>
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">P critical kN</div><div class="v amber" id="ebPcr">--</div></div>
                    <div class="stat"><div class="k">sigma critical MPa</div><div class="v green sm" id="ebScr">--</div></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="help" id="ebVerdict" style="margin-top:10px"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sec quiz"><div class="quiz" data-quiz="6"></div></div>

          <div class="sec ref"><ul class="refs">
            <li><b>Gere &amp; Goodno</b> &mdash; Mechanics of Materials, 9th ed., Ch. 11 (Columns). Cengage.</li>
            <li><b>Timoshenko &amp; Gere</b> &mdash; Theory of Elastic Stability, 2nd ed. McGraw-Hill.</li>
            <li><b>Virtual Labs (IIT)</b> &mdash; Strength of Materials: Buckling of Columns, mm-coep.vlabs.ac.in.</li>
          </ul></div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

<script is:inline>
(function () {
  function $(id) { return document.getElementById(id); }
  var DPR = Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio || 1, 2);

  function makeCtx(cv, logicalW, logicalH) {
    var cssW = cv.clientWidth || logicalW;
    var scale = cssW / logicalW;
    cv.width = Math.round(logicalW * DPR * scale);
    cv.height = Math.round(logicalH * DPR * scale);
    cv.style.height = (logicalH * scale) + 'px';
    var ctx = cv.getContext('2d');
    ctx.setTransform(DPR * scale, 0, 0, DPR * scale, 0, 0);
    return ctx;
  }
  function fmt(v, d) {
    if (v === null || v === undefined || !isFinite(v)) return '--';
    d = (d === undefined) ? 3 : d;
    var a = Math.abs(v);
    if (a !== 0 && (a < 1e-4 || a >= 1e6)) return v.toExponential(Math.min(d, 4));
    return (+v.toFixed(d)).toString();
  }
  function clamp(v, lo, hi) { return v < lo ? lo : (v > hi ? hi : v); }

  // ---- linear solver: Gaussian elimination with partial pivoting ----
  function solveLinear(Ain, bin) {
    var n = bin.length;
    var A = [], b = bin.slice();
    for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) A.push(Ain[i].slice());
    for (var col = 0; col < n; col++) {
      var piv = col;
      for (var r = col + 1; r < n; r++) if (Math.abs(A[r][col]) > Math.abs(A[piv][col])) piv = r;
      if (Math.abs(A[piv][col]) < 1e-12) return null;
      if (piv !== col) { var t = A[col]; A[col] = A[piv]; A[piv] = t; var tb = b[col]; b[col] = b[piv]; b[piv] = tb; }
      for (var r2 = col + 1; r2 < n; r2++) {
        var f = A[r2][col] / A[col][col];
        for (var c = col; c < n; c++) A[r2][c] -= f * A[col][c];
        b[r2] -= f * b[col];
      }
    }
    var x = new Array(n);
    for (var rb = n - 1; rb >= 0; rb--) {
      var s = b[rb];
      for (var cb = rb + 1; cb < n; cb++) s -= A[rb][cb] * x[cb];
      x[rb] = s / A[rb][rb];
    }
    return x;
  }

  // ---------- EXPERIMENT (sidebar) SWITCHING ----------
  var REDRAW = {};
  var items = document.querySelectorAll('.stx .exp-item');
  for (var t = 0; t < items.length; t++) {
    items[t].addEventListener('click', function () {
      var n = this.getAttribute('data-exp');
      var all = document.querySelectorAll('.stx .exp-item');
      for (var i = 0; i < all.length; i++) all[i].classList.remove('on');
      this.classList.add('on');
      var exps = document.querySelectorAll('.stx .exp');
      for (var j = 0; j < exps.length; j++) exps[j].classList.remove('on');
      $('exp-' + n).classList.add('on');
      window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
      if (REDRAW[n]) { try { REDRAW[n](); } catch (e) {} }
    });
  }

  // ---------- SECTION (tab) SWITCHING ----------
  var secbars = document.querySelectorAll('.stx .secbar');
  for (var s = 0; s < secbars.length; s++) {
    (function (bar) {
      var stabs = bar.querySelectorAll('.stab');
      var expEl = bar.parentNode;
      for (var k = 0; k < stabs.length; k++) {
        stabs[k].addEventListener('click', function () {
          var name = this.getAttribute('data-sec');
          for (var a = 0; a < stabs.length; a++) stabs[a].classList.remove('on');
          this.classList.add('on');
          var secs = expEl.querySelectorAll('.sec');
          for (var b = 0; b < secs.length; b++) secs[b].classList.remove('on');
          var target = expEl.querySelector('.sec.' + name);
          if (target) target.classList.add('on');
          if (name === 'sim') {
            var enr = expEl.id.split('-')[1];
            if (REDRAW[enr]) { try { REDRAW[enr](); } catch (e) {} }
          }
        });
      }
    })(secbars[s]);
  }

  // small helper for a seg control group
  function segGroup(container, attr, onPick) {
    var opts = container.querySelectorAll('[' + attr + ']');
    for (var i = 0; i < opts.length; i++) {
      (function (op) {
        op.addEventListener('click', function () {
          for (var j = 0; j < opts.length; j++) opts[j].classList.remove('on');
          op.classList.add('on');
          onPick(op.getAttribute(attr));
        });
      })(opts[i]);
    }
  }

  // ===================================================================
  // TRUSS MODEL BUILDER  (experiment 1)
  //   nodes: array of {x,y, support:'pin'|'roller'|null}
  //   members: array of [i,j]
  // ===================================================================
  function buildTruss(geo) {
    var nodes = [], members = [], h = 3, span = 4;
    function N(x, y, sup) { nodes.push({ x: x, y: y, support: sup || null }); return nodes.length - 1; }
    function M(a, b) { members.push([a, b]); }
    if (geo === 'tri') {
      var a0 = N(0, 0, 'pin'), a1 = N(8, 0, 'roller'), a2 = N(4, 4, null);
      M(a0, a1); M(a0, a2); M(a1, a2);
    } else if (geo === 'cant') {
      // cantilever bracket fixed to a wall on the left (pin + roller acting as wall)
      var b0 = N(0, 4, 'pin'), b1 = N(0, 0, 'roller');
      var c0 = N(4, 4, null), c1 = N(4, 0, null);
      var d0 = N(8, 4, null);
      M(b0, c0); M(b1, c1); M(c0, c1); M(b1, c0); M(c0, d0); M(c1, d0);
    } else {
      // 4-panel parallel-chord trusses, bottom chord at y=0, top at y=h
      var bot = [], top = [];
      for (var p = 0; p <= 4; p++) bot.push(N(p * span, 0, p === 0 ? 'pin' : (p === 4 ? 'roller' : null)));
      for (var q = 0; q <= 4; q++) top.push(N(q * span, h, null));
      for (var c = 0; c < 4; c++) { M(bot[c], bot[c + 1]); M(top[c], top[c + 1]); }
      for (var v = 0; v <= 4; v++) M(bot[v], top[v]);
      if (geo === 'warren') {
        M(bot[0], top[1]); M(top[1], bot[2]); M(bot[2], top[3]); M(top[3], bot[4]);
      } else if (geo === 'pratt') {
        M(top[0], bot[1]); M(top[1], bot[2]); M(bot[2], top[3]); M(bot[3], top[4]);
      } else { // howe
        M(bot[0], top[1]); M(bot[1], top[2]); M(top[2], bot[3]); M(top[3], bot[4]);
      }
    }
    return { nodes: nodes, members: members };
  }

  // assemble & solve truss as one equilibrium system
  function solveTruss(model, loads) {
    var nodes = model.nodes, members = model.members;
    var j = nodes.length, m = members.length;
    var reactCols = [];
    for (var i = 0; i < j; i++) {
      if (nodes[i].support === 'pin') { reactCols.push({ node: i, dir: 'x' }); reactCols.push({ node: i, dir: 'y' }); }
      else if (nodes[i].support === 'roller') { reactCols.push({ node: i, dir: 'y' }); }
    }
    var r = reactCols.length;
    var nEq = 2 * j, nUnk = m + r, det = m + r - 2 * j;
    var A = [], b = [];
    for (var e = 0; e < nEq; e++) { A.push(new Array(nUnk).fill(0)); b.push(0); }
    for (var mm = 0; mm < m; mm++) {
      var a = members[mm][0], c = members[mm][1];
      var dx = nodes[c].x - nodes[a].x, dy = nodes[c].y - nodes[a].y;
      var L = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy), ux = dx / L, uy = dy / L;
      A[2 * a][mm] += ux; A[2 * a + 1][mm] += uy;
      A[2 * c][mm] -= ux; A[2 * c + 1][mm] -= uy;
    }
    for (var rc = 0; rc < r; rc++) {
      var nd = reactCols[rc].node;
      if (reactCols[rc].dir === 'x') A[2 * nd][m + rc] += 1; else A[2 * nd + 1][m + rc] += 1;
    }
    for (var nd2 = 0; nd2 < j; nd2++) {
      var ld = loads[nd2];
      if (ld) { b[2 * nd2] -= ld.fx || 0; b[2 * nd2 + 1] -= ld.fy || 0; }
    }
    var x = (det === 0 && nUnk === nEq) ? solveLinear(A, b) : null;
    var forces = [], reactions = {};
    if (x) {
      for (var f = 0; f < m; f++) forces.push(x[f]);
      for (var g = 0; g < r; g++) reactions[reactCols[g].node + '_' + reactCols[g].dir] = x[m + g];
    }
    return { forces: forces, reactions: reactions, reactCols: reactCols, det: det, ok: !!x, m: m, j: j, r: r };
  }

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 1 — METHOD OF JOINTS
  // ===================================================================
  (function MethodOfJoints() {
    var cv = $('jtCv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 680, 430);
    var model = null, sol = null, loadNode = 0;

    function rebuild() {
      var geo = $('jtGeo').value;
      model = buildTruss(geo);
      var sel = $('jtJoint'); sel.innerHTML = '';
      var freeIdx = [];
      for (var i = 0; i < model.nodes.length; i++) {
        if (!model.nodes[i].support) {
          freeIdx.push(i);
          var o = document.createElement('option'); o.value = i;
          o.textContent = 'Joint ' + i + '  (' + model.nodes[i].x + ', ' + model.nodes[i].y + ')';
          sel.appendChild(o);
        }
      }
      loadNode = freeIdx.length ? freeIdx[Math.floor(freeIdx.length / 2)] : 0;
      sel.value = loadNode;
      sol = null;
      $('jtBody').innerHTML = '';
      stat('ready', '');
      draw();
    }
    function stat(txt, cls) { var b = $('jtStat'); b.textContent = txt; b.className = 'badge' + (cls ? ' ' + cls : ''); }

    function viewBox() {
      var xs = model.nodes.map(function (n) { return n.x; }), ys = model.nodes.map(function (n) { return n.y; });
      var x0 = Math.min.apply(null, xs), x1 = Math.max.apply(null, xs);
      var y0 = Math.min.apply(null, ys), y1 = Math.max.apply(null, ys);
      var pad = 72, W = 680, H = 430;
      var sx = (W - 2 * pad) / ((x1 - x0) || 1);
      var sy = (H - 2 * pad - 20) / ((y1 - y0) || 1);
      var sc = Math.min(sx, sy);
      function P(x, y) { return [pad + (x - x0) * sc, H - pad - (y - y0) * sc]; }
      return { P: P };
    }

    function arrow(x0, y0, x1, y1, col, label) {
      ctx.strokeStyle = col; ctx.fillStyle = col; ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x0, y0); ctx.lineTo(x1, y1); ctx.stroke();
      var ang = Math.atan2(y1 - y0, x1 - x0);
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x1, y1);
      ctx.lineTo(x1 - 8 * Math.cos(ang - 0.4), y1 - 8 * Math.sin(ang - 0.4));
      ctx.lineTo(x1 - 8 * Math.cos(ang + 0.4), y1 - 8 * Math.sin(ang + 0.4));
      ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      if (label) { ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'left'; ctx.fillText(label, x1 + 6, (y0 + y1) / 2 + 3); }
    }

    function draw() {
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, 680, 430);
      var P = viewBox().P;
      var maxF = 0;
      if (sol && sol.ok) for (var i = 0; i < sol.forces.length; i++) maxF = Math.max(maxF, Math.abs(sol.forces[i]));
      for (var mm = 0; mm < model.members.length; mm++) {
        var a = model.members[mm][0], c = model.members[mm][1];
        var pa = P(model.nodes[a].x, model.nodes[a].y), pc = P(model.nodes[c].x, model.nodes[c].y);
        var col = '#3a3a48', lw = 2;
        if (sol && sol.ok) {
          var f = sol.forces[mm];
          if (Math.abs(f) < 1e-6) { col = '#3a3a48'; lw = 2; }
          else if (f > 0) { col = '#fca5a5'; lw = 2 + 5 * Math.abs(f) / (maxF || 1); }
          else { col = '#67e8f9'; lw = 2 + 5 * Math.abs(f) / (maxF || 1); }
        }
        ctx.strokeStyle = col; ctx.lineWidth = lw;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pa[0], pa[1]); ctx.lineTo(pc[0], pc[1]); ctx.stroke();
        if (sol && sol.ok) {
          var mx = (pa[0] + pc[0]) / 2, my = (pa[1] + pc[1]) / 2;
          ctx.fillStyle = (col === '#3a3a48') ? '#9aa0aa' : col;
          ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
          ctx.fillText((sol.forces[mm] >= 0 ? '+' : '') + sol.forces[mm].toFixed(1), mx, my - 4);
        }
      }
      for (var n = 0; n < model.nodes.length; n++) {
        var p = P(model.nodes[n].x, model.nodes[n].y);
        if (model.nodes[n].support) {
          ctx.fillStyle = '#86efac';
          ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(p[0], p[1]); ctx.lineTo(p[0] - 9, p[1] + 14); ctx.lineTo(p[0] + 9, p[1] + 14); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
          ctx.fillStyle = '#9aa0aa'; ctx.font = '9px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
          ctx.fillText(model.nodes[n].support === 'pin' ? 'pin' : 'roller', p[0], p[1] + 26);
          if (sol && sol.ok) {
            var ry = sol.reactions[n + '_y'], rx = sol.reactions[n + '_x'];
            if (ry !== undefined && Math.abs(ry) > 1e-6) arrow(p[0], p[1] + 14, p[0], p[1] + 14 - Math.sign(ry) * 28, '#86efac', fmt(ry, 1));
            if (rx !== undefined && Math.abs(rx) > 1e-6) arrow(p[0], p[1], p[0] + Math.sign(rx) * 28, p[1], '#86efac', fmt(rx, 1));
          }
        }
      }
      for (var jn = 0; jn < model.nodes.length; jn++) {
        var q = P(model.nodes[jn].x, model.nodes[jn].y);
        ctx.fillStyle = '#11131a'; ctx.strokeStyle = '#cfd6da'; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(q[0], q[1], 5, 0, 7); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
        ctx.fillStyle = '#9aa0aa'; ctx.font = '9px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
        ctx.fillText(jn, q[0], q[1] - 9);
      }
      var lp = P(model.nodes[loadNode].x, model.nodes[loadNode].y);
      var P0 = parseFloat($('jtP').value);
      arrow(lp[0], lp[1] - 6, lp[0], lp[1] - 46, '#fbbf24', P0 + ' kN');
    }

    function solve() {
      var loads = {};
      loads[loadNode] = { fx: 0, fy: -parseFloat($('jtP').value) };
      sol = solveTruss(model, loads);
      $('jtM').textContent = sol.m; $('jtJ').textContent = sol.j;
      $('jtDet').textContent = sol.det + (sol.det === 0 ? ' (determinate)' : (sol.det > 0 ? ' (redundant)' : ' (mechanism)'));
      if (!sol.ok) { stat('indeterminate', 'bad'); $('jtBody').innerHTML = ''; draw(); return; }
      var maxF = 0; for (var i = 0; i < sol.forces.length; i++) maxF = Math.max(maxF, Math.abs(sol.forces[i]));
      $('jtMax').textContent = fmt(maxF, 2) + ' kN';
      var pinNode = -1, rollNode = -1;
      for (var k = 0; k < model.nodes.length; k++) { if (model.nodes[k].support === 'pin') pinNode = k; if (model.nodes[k].support === 'roller') rollNode = k; }
      $('jtAx').textContent = fmt(sol.reactions[pinNode + '_x'] || 0, 2);
      $('jtAy').textContent = fmt(sol.reactions[pinNode + '_y'] || 0, 2);
      $('jtBy').textContent = fmt(sol.reactions[rollNode + '_y'] || 0, 2);
      var P0 = parseFloat($('jtP').value);
      var px = model.nodes[pinNode].x;
      var Mres = (-P0) * (model.nodes[loadNode].x - px) + (sol.reactions[rollNode + '_y'] || 0) * (model.nodes[rollNode].x - px);
      $('jtChk').textContent = Math.abs(Mres) < 1e-6 ? 'OK (0)' : fmt(Mres, 4);
      $('jtChk').className = 'v sm' + (Math.abs(Mres) < 1e-3 ? ' green' : ' red');
      var rows = '';
      for (var mm = 0; mm < model.members.length; mm++) {
        var f = sol.forces[mm];
        var st = Math.abs(f) < 1e-6 ? 'zero' : (f > 0 ? 'Tension' : 'Compression');
        var cls = Math.abs(f) < 1e-6 ? 'z' : (f > 0 ? 't' : 'c');
        rows += '<tr><td class="lbl">U' + model.members[mm][0] + '-' + model.members[mm][1] + '</td><td class="' + cls + '">' + (f >= 0 ? '+' : '') + fmt(f, 2) + '</td><td class="' + cls + '">' + st + '</td></tr>';
      }
      $('jtBody').innerHTML = rows;
      stat('solved', '');
      draw();
    }

    $('jtGeo').addEventListener('change', rebuild);
    $('jtP').addEventListener('input', function () { $('jtPv').textContent = this.value; draw(); });
    $('jtJoint').addEventListener('change', function () { loadNode = parseInt(this.value, 10); draw(); });
    $('jtSolve').addEventListener('click', solve);
    $('jtClear').addEventListener('click', function () {
      sol = null; $('jtBody').innerHTML = '';
      $('jtMax').textContent = '--'; $('jtAx').textContent = '--'; $('jtAy').textContent = '--'; $('jtBy').textContent = '--'; $('jtChk').textContent = '--';
      stat('ready', ''); draw();
    });

    REDRAW['1'] = function () { ctx = makeCtx(cv, 680, 430); draw(); };
    rebuild();
  })();

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 2 — METHOD OF SECTIONS  (Pratt truss, 4 panels)
  // ===================================================================
  (function MethodOfSections() {
    var cv = $('scCv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 680, 430);
    var span = 4, h = 3, nPanel = 4;
    var nodes = [], members = [], memberName = [], bot = [], top = [];
    function N(x, y) { nodes.push({ x: x, y: y }); return nodes.length - 1; }
    function M(a, b, nm) { members.push([a, b]); memberName.push(nm); }

    (function buildModel() {
      for (var p = 0; p <= nPanel; p++) bot.push(N(p * span, 0));
      for (var q = 0; q <= nPanel; q++) top.push(N(q * span, h));
      for (var c = 0; c < nPanel; c++) { M(bot[c], bot[c + 1], 'L' + c + (c + 1)); M(top[c], top[c + 1], 'U' + c + (c + 1)); }
      for (var v = 0; v <= nPanel; v++) M(bot[v], top[v], 'V' + v);
      M(top[0], bot[1], 'D01'); M(top[1], bot[2], 'D12'); M(bot[2], top[3], 'D23'); M(bot[3], top[4], 'D34');
    })();

    var reactions = { Ay: 0, By: 0 };
    var curLoadNode = bot[Math.floor(nPanel / 2)];

    function computeReactions(P) {
      var L = nPanel * span, x = nodes[curLoadNode].x;
      reactions.By = P * x / L;
      reactions.Ay = P - reactions.By;
    }

    function crossedMembers(cut) {
      var xcut = (cut + 1.5) * span; // mid-panel cut line; cut=0 -> x=1.5*span (panel 1|2)
      var crossed = [];
      for (var i = 0; i < members.length; i++) {
        var a = members[i][0], b = members[i][1];
        var xa = nodes[a].x, xb = nodes[b].x;
        if ((xa < xcut && xb > xcut) || (xb < xcut && xa > xcut)) crossed.push(i);
      }
      return { list: crossed, xcut: xcut };
    }

    function fullSolve(P) {
      var model = { nodes: nodes.map(function (n) { return { x: n.x, y: n.y, support: null }; }), members: members };
      model.nodes[bot[0]].support = 'pin'; model.nodes[bot[nPanel]].support = 'roller';
      var loads = {}; loads[curLoadNode] = { fx: 0, fy: -P };
      return solveTruss(model, loads);
    }

    function vb() {
      var pad = 72, W = 680, H = 430, x1 = nPanel * span;
      var sc = Math.min((W - 2 * pad) / x1, (H - 2 * pad) / h);
      function P(x, y) { return [pad + x * sc, H - pad - y * sc]; }
      return { P: P };
    }

    var lastTarget = -1;

    function drawSupport(p, kind) {
      ctx.fillStyle = '#86efac';
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(p[0], p[1]); ctx.lineTo(p[0] - 8, p[1] + 12); ctx.lineTo(p[0] + 8, p[1] + 12); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      ctx.fillStyle = '#9aa0aa'; ctx.font = '9px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center'; ctx.fillText(kind, p[0], p[1] + 24);
    }
    function arrow(x0, y0, x1, y1, col, label) {
      ctx.strokeStyle = col; ctx.fillStyle = col; ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x0, y0); ctx.lineTo(x1, y1); ctx.stroke();
      var ang = Math.atan2(y1 - y0, x1 - x0);
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x1, y1);
      ctx.lineTo(x1 - 7 * Math.cos(ang - 0.4), y1 - 7 * Math.sin(ang - 0.4));
      ctx.lineTo(x1 - 7 * Math.cos(ang + 0.4), y1 - 7 * Math.sin(ang + 0.4));
      ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      if (label) { ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'left'; ctx.fillText(label, x1 + 6, (y0 + y1) / 2 + 3); }
    }

    function draw() {
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, 680, 430);
      var P = vb().P;
      var cut = parseInt($('scCut').value, 10);
      var cm = crossedMembers(cut), xcut = cm.xcut;
      var pTop = P(xcut, h + 0.6), pBot = P(xcut, -0.6);
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(167,139,250,0.07)';
      ctx.fillRect(36, 18, pTop[0] - 36, 412 - 18);
      for (var i = 0; i < members.length; i++) {
        var a = members[i][0], b = members[i][1];
        var pa = P(nodes[a].x, nodes[a].y), pb = P(nodes[b].x, nodes[b].y);
        var col = '#3a3a48', lw = 2;
        if (cm.list.indexOf(i) >= 0) { col = '#cfd6da'; lw = 2.5; }
        if (i === lastTarget) { col = '#fbbf24'; lw = 4; }
        ctx.strokeStyle = col; ctx.lineWidth = lw;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pa[0], pa[1]); ctx.lineTo(pb[0], pb[1]); ctx.stroke();
        if (cm.list.indexOf(i) >= 0) {
          var mx = (pa[0] + pb[0]) / 2, my = (pa[1] + pb[1]) / 2;
          ctx.fillStyle = (i === lastTarget) ? '#fbbf24' : '#cfd6da'; ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
          ctx.fillText(memberName[i], mx, my - 5);
        }
      }
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#fca5a5'; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5; ctx.setLineDash([6, 5]);
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pTop[0], pTop[1]); ctx.lineTo(pBot[0], pBot[1]); ctx.stroke(); ctx.setLineDash([]);
      for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        var q = P(nodes[n].x, nodes[n].y);
        ctx.fillStyle = '#11131a'; ctx.strokeStyle = '#cfd6da'; ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
        ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(q[0], q[1], 4, 0, 7); ctx.fill(); ctx.stroke();
      }
      var sa = P(nodes[bot[0]].x, 0), sb = P(nodes[bot[nPanel]].x, 0);
      drawSupport(sa, 'pin'); drawSupport(sb, 'roller');
      arrow(sa[0], sa[1] + 12, sa[0], sa[1] + 12 - 28, '#86efac', 'Ay ' + fmt(reactions.Ay, 1));
      arrow(sb[0], sb[1] + 12, sb[0], sb[1] + 12 - 28, '#86efac', 'By ' + fmt(reactions.By, 1));
      var lp = P(nodes[curLoadNode].x, 0);
      arrow(lp[0], lp[1] - 6, lp[0], lp[1] - 42, '#fbbf24', parseFloat($('scP').value) + ' kN');
    }

    function refreshMembers() {
      var cm = crossedMembers(parseInt($('scCut').value, 10));
      var sel = $('scMem'); sel.innerHTML = '';
      for (var i = 0; i < cm.list.length; i++) {
        var o = document.createElement('option'); o.value = cm.list[i]; o.textContent = memberName[cm.list[i]];
        sel.appendChild(o);
      }
    }
    function log(html) { $('scLog').innerHTML = html; }

    function solveMember() {
      var P = parseFloat($('scP').value);
      computeReactions(P);
      var fullSol = fullSolve(P);
      var target = parseInt($('scMem').value, 10);
      lastTarget = target;
      var cm = crossedMembers(parseInt($('scCut').value, 10)), xcut = cm.xcut;
      var extFy = reactions.Ay;
      if (nodes[curLoadNode].x < xcut) extFy -= P;
      var a = members[target][0], b = members[target][1];
      var dx = nodes[b].x - nodes[a].x, dy = nodes[b].y - nodes[a].y, L = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
      var horiz = Math.abs(dy) < 1e-6, vert = Math.abs(dx) < 1e-6;
      var f = fullSol.forces[target];
      var html = '';
      html += '<div class="ln"><b>Free body:</b> portion left of x = ' + xcut + ' m</div>';
      html += '<div class="ln">Reaction Ay = P&middot;x_load/L = ' + P + '&middot;' + nodes[curLoadNode].x + '/' + (nPanel * span) + ' = ' + fmt(reactions.Ay, 2) + ' kN (up)</div>';
      html += '<div class="ln">Net vertical force on free body (excl. cut members) = ' + fmt(extFy, 2) + ' kN</div>';
      if (horiz) {
        html += '<div class="ln">' + memberName[target] + ' is a chord. Take Sum M about the joint where the diagonal and the other chord meet; lever arm = panel height = ' + h + ' m.</div>';
        html += '<div class="ln">' + memberName[target] + ' &middot; ' + h + ' = (moment of Ay and any load on the free body about that joint)</div>';
      } else if (vert) {
        html += '<div class="ln">' + memberName[target] + ' is a vertical. Sum Fy on the free body gives it directly (the cut chords are horizontal).</div>';
        html += '<div class="ln">Sum Fy = 0 &rArr; ' + fmt(extFy, 2) + ' + ' + memberName[target] + ' = 0</div>';
      } else {
        var sinT = Math.abs(dy) / L;
        html += '<div class="ln">' + memberName[target] + ' is a diagonal. Sum Fy on the free body isolates its vertical component (the chords are horizontal).</div>';
        html += '<div class="ln">Sum Fy = 0 &rArr; ' + fmt(extFy, 2) + ' + ' + memberName[target] + '&middot;sin(theta) = 0,&nbsp; sin(theta) = ' + fmt(sinT, 3) + '</div>';
      }
      html += '<div class="ln ' + (Math.abs(f) < 1e-9 ? 'warn' : 'ok') + '"><b>Result: ' + memberName[target] + ' = ' + (f >= 0 ? '+' : '') + fmt(f, 2) + ' kN  (' + (Math.abs(f) < 1e-6 ? 'zero-force' : (f > 0 ? 'Tension' : 'Compression')) + ')</b></div>';
      log(html);
      $('scAy').textContent = fmt(reactions.Ay, 2);
      $('scBy').textContent = fmt(reactions.By, 2);
      $('scF').textContent = (f >= 0 ? '+' : '') + fmt(f, 2) + ' kN';
      $('scState').textContent = Math.abs(f) < 1e-6 ? 'zero-force' : (f > 0 ? 'Tension' : 'Compression');
      $('scStat').textContent = 'solved'; $('scStat').className = 'badge';
      draw();
    }

    function showAll() {
      var P = parseFloat($('scP').value);
      computeReactions(P);
      var fullSol = fullSolve(P);
      lastTarget = -1;
      var cm = crossedMembers(parseInt($('scCut').value, 10));
      var html = '<div class="ln"><b>Forces in the ' + cm.list.length + ' members crossed by the cut:</b></div>';
      for (var i = 0; i < cm.list.length; i++) {
        var f = fullSol.forces[cm.list[i]];
        html += '<div class="ln">' + memberName[cm.list[i]] + ' = ' + (f >= 0 ? '+' : '') + fmt(f, 2) + ' kN (' + (Math.abs(f) < 1e-6 ? 'zero' : (f > 0 ? 'Tension' : 'Compression')) + ')</div>';
      }
      log(html);
      $('scAy').textContent = fmt(reactions.Ay, 2); $('scBy').textContent = fmt(reactions.By, 2);
      draw();
    }

    $('scP').addEventListener('input', function () { $('scPv').textContent = this.value; computeReactions(parseFloat(this.value)); draw(); });
    $('scCut').addEventListener('change', function () { refreshMembers(); lastTarget = -1; draw(); });
    $('scSolve').addEventListener('click', solveMember);
    $('scAll').addEventListener('click', showAll);

    REDRAW['2'] = function () { ctx = makeCtx(cv, 680, 430); computeReactions(parseFloat($('scP').value)); refreshMembers(); draw(); };
    computeReactions(parseFloat($('scP').value));
    refreshMembers();
    draw();
  })();

  // ===================================================================
  // EXPERIMENT 3 — SFD / BMD
  // ===================================================================
  (function ShearMoment() {
    var cv = $('sfCv'); if (!cv) return;
    var ctx = makeCtx(cv, 680, 500);
    var beam = 'ss';
    var L = 8;
    var loads = []; // {kind:'P'|'w'|'M', mag, a, b}

    function reactions() {
      if (beam === 'ss') {
        var sumF = 0, sumMA = 0, sumCouple = 0;
        for (var i = 0; i < loads.length; i++) {
          var ld = loads[i];
          if (ld.kind === 'P') { sumF += ld.mag; sumMA += ld.mag * ld.a; }
          else if (ld.kind === 'w') { var W = ld.mag * (ld.b - ld.a); var xc = (ld.a + ld.b) / 2; sumF += W; sumMA += W * xc; }
          else if (ld.kind === 'M') { sumCouple += ld.mag; }
        }
        var RB = (sumMA + sumCouple) / L;
        return { RA: sumF - RB, RB: RB };
      } else {
        var sumF = 0, sumM = 0, sumCouple = 0;
        for (var j = 0; j < loads.length; j++) {
          var l2 = loads[j];
          if (l2.kind === 'P') { sumF += l2.mag; sumM += l2.mag * l2.a; }
          else if (l2.kind === 'w') { var W2 = l2.mag * (l2.b - l2.a); sumF += W2; sumM += W2 * (l2.a + l2.b) / 2; }
          else if (l2.kind === 'M') { sumCouple += l2.mag; }
        }
        return { RA: sumF, MA: sumM + sumCouple };
      }
    }

    function VM(x) {
      var R = reactions();
      var V = 0, M = 0;
      if (beam === 'ss') { V += R.RA; M += R.RA * x; }
      else { V += R.RA; M += R.RA * x - R.MA; }
      for (var i = 0; i < loads.length; i++) {
        var ld = loads[i];
        if (ld.kind === 'P') { if (ld.a <= x) { V -= ld.mag; M -= ld.mag * (x - ld.a); } }
        else if (ld.kind === 'w') {
          if (x > ld.a) {
            var x2 = Math.min(x, ld.b), len = x2 - ld.a, Wp = ld.mag * len;
            V -= Wp; M -= Wp * (x - (ld.a + x2) / 2);
          }
        } else if (ld.kind === 'M') { if (ld.a < x) { M -= ld.mag; } }
      }
      return { V: V, M: M };
    }

    function sample(N) {
      var xs = [], Vs = [], Ms = [];
      for (var i = 0; i <= N; i++) {
        var x = L * i / N;
        var vm = VM(x + 1e-9);
        xs.push(x); Vs.push(vm.V); Ms.push(vm.M);
      }
      return { xs: xs, Vs: Vs, Ms: Ms };
    }

    function triSupport(x, y) { ctx.fillStyle = '#86efac'; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x, y + 2); ctx.lineTo(x - 9, y + 16); ctx.lineTo(x + 9, y + 16); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill(); }
    function circSupport(x, y) {
      ctx.fillStyle = '#86efac'; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x, y + 2); ctx.lineTo(x - 9, y + 14); ctx.lineTo(x + 9, y + 14); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#86efac'; ctx.lineWidth = 1; ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(x - 4, y + 18, 2.5, 0, 7); ctx.moveTo(x + 6.5, y + 18); ctx.arc(x + 4, y + 18, 2.5, 0, 7); ctx.stroke();
    }
    function rArrow(x, y, mag) {
      if (Math.abs(mag) < 1e-6) return;
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#86efac'; ctx.fillStyle = '#86efac'; ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x, y + 24); ctx.lineTo(x, y + 2); ctx.stroke();
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x, y + 2); ctx.lineTo(x - 4, y + 10); ctx.lineTo(x + 4, y + 10); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      ctx.font = '9px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center'; ctx.fillText(fmt(mag, 1), x, y + 36);
    }

    function bx(x) { var padL = 50, padR = 24, beamW = 680 - padL - padR; return padL + x / L * beamW; }

    function drawDiagram(xs, ys, cy, halfH, col, title) {
      var padL = 50, padR = 24;
      var ymax = 1e-6; for (var i = 0; i < ys.length; i++) ymax = Math.max(ymax, Math.abs(ys[i]));
      var sc = (halfH - 6) / ymax;
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#2a2a35'; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(padL, cy); ctx.lineTo(680 - padR, cy); ctx.stroke();
      ctx.fillStyle = col + '22';
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(bx(xs[0]), cy);
      for (var k = 0; k < xs.length; k++) ctx.lineTo(bx(xs[k]), cy - ys[k] * sc);
      ctx.lineTo(bx(xs[xs.length - 1]), cy); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
      ctx.strokeStyle = col; ctx.lineWidth = 2; ctx.beginPath();
      for (var j = 0; j < xs.length; j++) { var X = bx(xs[j]), Y = cy - ys[j] * sc; if (j === 0) ctx.moveTo(X, Y); else ctx.lineTo(X, Y); }
      ctx.stroke();
      ctx.fillStyle = col; ctx.font = '11px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'left';
      ctx.fillText(title, padL, cy - halfH - 6);
      var pk = 0, px = 0; for (var p = 0; p < ys.length; p++) if (Math.abs(ys[p]) > Math.abs(pk)) { pk = ys[p]; px = xs[p]; }
      ctx.fillStyle = col; ctx.textAlign = 'center'; ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono';
      ctx.fillText(fmt(pk, 1), bx(px), cy - pk * sc + (pk >= 0 ? -4 : 12));
    }

    function draw() {
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, 680, 500);
      var R = reactions();
      var beamY = 70;
      ctx.strokeStyle = '#cfd6da'; ctx.lineWidth = 3;
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(bx(0), beamY); ctx.lineTo(bx(L), beamY); ctx.stroke();
      if (beam === 'ss') {
        triSupport(bx(0), beamY); circSupport(bx(L), beamY);
        rArrow(bx(0), beamY + 16, R.RA); rArrow(bx(L), beamY + 16, R.RB);
      } else {
        ctx.fillStyle = '#3a3a48'; ctx.fillRect(bx(0) - 10, beamY - 26, 10, 52);
        ctx.strokeStyle = '#9aa0aa'; ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        for (var w = 0; w < 6; w++) { ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(bx(0) - 10, beamY - 26 + w * 10); ctx.lineTo(bx(0) - 18, beamY - 26 + w * 10 - 6); ctx.stroke(); }
        rArrow(bx(0), beamY + 16, R.RA);
      }
      ctx.font = '10px Geist Mono'; ctx.textAlign = 'center';
      for (var i = 0; i < loads.length; i++) {
        var ld = loads[i];
        if (ld.kind === 'P') {
          ctx.strokeStyle = '#fbbf24'; ctx.fillStyle = '#fbbf24'; ctx.lineWidth = 2;
          ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(bx(ld.a), beamY - 40); ctx.lineTo(bx(ld.a), beamY - 3); ctx.stroke();
          ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(bx(ld.a), beamY - 3); ctx.lineTo(bx(ld.a) - 5, beamY - 12); ctx.lineTo(bx(ld.a) + 5, beamY - 12); ctx.closePath(); ctx.fill();
          ctx.fillText(ld.mag + 'kN', bx(ld.a), beamY - 44);
        } else if (ld.kind === 'w') {
          ctx.strokeStyle = '#a78bfa'; ctx.fillStyle = '#a78bfa'; ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
          ctx.strokeRect(bx(ld.a), beamY - 30, bx(ld.b) - bx(ld.a), 27);
          for (var k = bx(ld.a) + 6; k <= bx(ld.b); k += 14) { ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(k, beamY - 28); ctx.lineTo(k, beamY - 5); ctx.stroke(); }
          ctx.fillText(ld.mag + 'kN/m', (bx(ld.a) + bx(ld.b)) / 2, beamY - 34);
        } else {
          ctx.strokeStyle = '#fca5a5'; ctx.fillStyle = '#fca5a5'; ctx.lineWidth = 2;
          ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(bx(ld.a), beamY, 12, -2.2, 1.6); ctx.stroke();
          ctx.fillText(ld.mag + 'kNm', bx(ld.a), beamY - 22);
        }
      }
      var smp = sample(400);
      drawDiagram(smp.xs, smp.Vs, 200, 110, '#67e8f9', 'Shear Force  V (kN)');
      drawDiagram(smp.xs, smp.Ms, 370, 110, '#fbbf24', 'Bending Moment  M (kN m)');
      var Vmax = 0, Mmax = 0, xM = 0;
      for (var sx = 0; sx < smp.xs.length; sx++) {
        if (Math.abs(smp.Vs[sx]) > Math.abs(Vmax)) Vmax = smp.Vs[sx];
        if (Math.abs(smp.Ms[sx]) > Math.abs(Mmax)) { Mmax = smp.Ms[sx]; xM = smp.xs[sx]; }
      }
      $('sfVmax').textContent = fmt(Vmax, 2) + ' kN';
      $('sfMmax').textContent = fmt(Mmax, 2) + ' @ ' + fmt(xM, 2) + 'm';
      $('sfRA').textContent = fmt(R.RA, 2) + ' kN';
      $('sfRB').textContent = beam === 'ss' ? (fmt(R.RB, 2) + ' kN') : (fmt(R.MA, 2) + ' kNm');
      $('sfRBk').textContent = beam === 'ss' ? 'Reaction R(B)' : 'Fixing moment M(A)';
    }

    function rebuildTable() {
      var rows = '';
      for (var i = 0; i < loads.length; i++) {
        var ld = loads[i];
        var at = ld.kind === 'w' ? (ld.a + '-' + ld.b) : ('' + ld.a);
        rows += '<tr><td class="lbl">' + (ld.kind === 'P' ? 'Point' : (ld.kind === 'w' ? 'UDL' : 'Moment')) + '</td><td>' + ld.mag + '</td><td>' + at + '</td><td><span class="btn red" style="padding:2px 7px;font-size:9px" data-del="' + i + '">x</span></td></tr>';
      }
      $('sfBody').innerHTML = rows;
      var dels = $('sfBody').querySelectorAll('[data-del]');
      for (var d = 0; d < dels.length; d++) dels[d].addEventListener('click', function () { loads.splice(parseInt(this.getAttribute('data-del'), 10), 1); rebuildTable(); draw(); });
    }

    function addLoad() {
      var k = $('sfKind').value;
      var mag = parseFloat($('sfMag').value), a = parseFloat($('sfA').value), b = parseFloat($('sfB').value);
      if (!isFinite(mag)) return;
      a = clamp(a, 0, L);
      if (k === 'w') { b = clamp(b, 0, L); if (b <= a) b = Math.min(L, a + 1); loads.push({ kind: 'w', mag: mag, a: a, b: b }); }
      else if (k === 'P') loads.push({ kind: 'P', mag: mag, a: a });
      else loads.push({ kind: 'M', mag: mag, a: a });
